 The wife of late singer Nomoreloss, Adeola Osinuga, is dead. Family sources said she died after battling a chronic ailment Fibromyalgia for over four years. She was an On Air Personality (OAP) with Rhythm 93.7 FM before she took ill. It was gathered the ailment took a big toll, keeping her hospitalised and away from work.  Medical experts define fibromyalgia as a rheumatic disease characterised by muscular or musculoskeletal discomfort with stiffness and localised tenderness at specific points on the body. Nomoreless died in March 2016 of pneumonia. They got married in 2008 and had a daughter, Mo, in 2011.